Accumulation rate values were calculated de-straining the depth-age scale of Meese, Sowers, et al. 3 Versions correspond to 3 different ice dynamics situations, as described in Cuffey and Clow (1997). Each one assumes a different value for the retreat distance of the ice sheet margin during the deglaciation.

Accumulation of snow/ice per year [cm/a] (Acc rate) * PI: Cuffey, Kurt M * METHOD/DEVICE: see reference(s) * COMMENT: ice-equivalent accumulation rate, calculated assuming a 50 kilometer retreat of the ice sheet margin during deglaciation

Accumulation of snow/ice per year [cm/a] (Acc rate) * PI: Cuffey, Kurt M * METHOD/DEVICE: see reference(s) * COMMENT: ice-equivalent accumulation rate, calculated assuming a 100 kilometer retreat of the ice sheet margin during deglaciation.

Accumulation of snow/ice per year [cm/a] (Acc rate) * PI: Cuffey, Kurt M * METHOD/DEVICE: see reference(s) * COMMENT: ice-equivalent accumulation rate, calculated assuming a 200 kilometer retreat of the ice sheet margin during deglaciation; this is probably the most accurate of the three
